[[File:H. J. Beemer, Montreal, QC, 1881.jpg|thumb|upright|<center>H. J. Beemer, 1881</center>]] '''Horace Jansen Beemer''' ([[Circa|c.]] 1845 &ndash; July 22, 1912) was a railway contractor and businessman.
There is little known of Beemer before he came to Canada in the 1870s and was employed on the [[Welland Canal]]. He was soon involved in contracts of his own including a municipal water system in [[Quebec City]]<ref>http://histoire-du-quebec.ca/horace-beemer-et-son-aqueduc/</ref> and a railway contract with the [[:fr:Quebec and Lake St-John Railway]]<ref>http://hedley-junction.blogspot.com/2010/11/presentation-du-reseau.html</ref>. Up until about 1900, his business interest grew and prospered. After that time, his activity and influence diminished.
While Horace Beemer never became a top level decision-maker and financier, he did contribute substantially to the construction of railways and operation of related businesses. <gallery mode = packed> Roberval BAnQ P560S1P336.jpg|<center>Hotel Roberval or Beemer Hotel</center> </gallery> ==References== {{Reflist}}
==External links== *[http://www.biographi.ca/009004-119.01-e.php?&id_nbr=7198 Biography at the ''Dictionary of Canadian Biography Online'']
