'''Jozef Cornu''' (born 1944) is a Belgian [[engineer]] and business executive, and former CEO of the [[National Railway Company of Belgium]].<ref name="IPO 2013">[http://www.antwerpmanagementschool.be/nl/news/2013/9/20/jo-cornu,-alumnus-executive-mba,-wordt-nieuwe-ceo-bij-nmbs.aspx Jo Cornu wordt nieuwe CEO bij NMBS: Alumnus Executive MBA 1981-1983] at ''antwerpmanagementschool.be'' news 2013/9/20</ref>
== Biography == Cornu graduated as [[Master of Science]] in [[electrical engineering]] and [[mechanics]] at the [[Katholieke Universiteit Leuven]] and he obtained a PhD in electronics at the [[Carlton University]] in Ottawa, Canada. From 1981 to 1983 he attended the Postgraduate Program Business-executive at the [[Antwerp Management School]].<ref name="IPO 2013"/>
From 1982 up to 1984 Cornu was CEO of [[AMI Semiconductor|Mietec]] in [[Oudenaarde]] and afterwards General Manager of [[Bell Telephone Company|Bell Telephone]] until 1987. From 1988 up to 1995 he was a member of the Executive Board committee of [[Alcatel-Lucent|Alcatel]] plc and from 1995 up to 1999 COO of Alcatel Telecom. Afterwards he became President of the Board of Directors of Alcatel.
Since 2005 Jo Cornu is President of [[ISTAG]]-group (Information Society Technologies Advisory Group) of the [[European Commission]]. In 2005, he was a member of the group which wrote the [[Aho report]]. From 1 December 2007 to 27 April 2010 he was CEO of [[Agfa-Gevaert]].<ref>[http://www.trends.be/nl/economie/mensen/4-239-45913/jo-cornu-nieuwe-ceo-agfa-gevaert.html Jo Cornu nieuwe CEO Agfa-Gevaert] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071203070317/http://www.trends.be/nl/economie/mensen/4-239-45913/jo-cornu-nieuwe-ceo-agfa-gevaert.html |date=3 December 2007 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Auteur: lob |url=http://www.nieuwsblad.be/Article/Detail.aspx?articleid=DMF30112007_016 |title=Agfa-Gevaert benoemt Jo Cornu tot ceo |publisher=Nieuwsblad.be |date=2007-11-30 |accessdate=2014-03-28}}</ref>
